## Why This Is Asked
Tests palindrome enumeration and multi-substring DP; requires handling non-overlapping constraints and reconstruction.

## Key Concepts
- Palindrome precomputation isPal[l][r] in O(n^2).
- DP states dp[i][t] track best total length for first i chars and t palindromes.
- Transition closes a palindrome ending at i via isPal[l][i-1], adding (i-l+1).
- Backpointers enable reconstruction of the endpoints.
- Time: O(n^2 k); Space: O(n^2 + nk).

## Code Example
