## Why This Problem Matters
This problem assesses sophisticated dynamic programming techniques by combining palindrome preprocessing, optimal substructure for non-overlapping segment selection, and explicit solution reconstruction. It integrates preprocessing with suffix-based DP while requiring careful index management.

## Key Concepts
- Palindrome table (isPal) DP preprocessing for O(1) palindrome queries
- 2D DP with optimal substructure and complete solution reconstruction
- Complexity analysis: Time O(n²k), Space O(n² + nk)

## Code Example
```javascript
function maxPalBlocks(s, k) {
  const n = s.length;
  const isPal = Array.from({length: n}, () => Array(n).fill(false));

  // Precompute palindrome table
  for (let len = 1; len <= n; len++) {
    for (let l = 0; l + len <= n; l++) {
      const r = l + len - 1;
      isPal[l][r] = (s[l] === s[r] && (len <= 2 || isPal[l+1][r-1]));
    }
  }

  // Initialize DP tables
  const dp = Array.from({length: n + 1}, () => Array(k + 1).fill(0));
  const trace = Array.from({length: n + 1}, () => Array(k + 1).fill(null));

  // Fill DP table
  for (let i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    for (let t = 1; t <= k; t++) {
      dp[i][t] = dp[i + 1][t];
      trace[i][t] = {type: 'skip'};

      for (let j = i; j < n; j++) {
        if (isPal[i][j]) {
          const val = (j - i + 1) + dp[j + 1][t - 1];
          if (val > dp[i][t]) {
            dp[i][t] = val;
            trace[i][t] = {type: 'take', l: i, r: j};
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  // Reconstruct solution
  const blocks = [];
  let i = 0, t = k;
  while (t > 0 && i < n) {
    const choice = trace[i][t];
    if (choice.type === 'take') {
      blocks.push([choice.l, choice.r]);
      i = choice.r + 1;
      t--;
    } else {
      i++;
    }
  }

  return {maxLength: dp[0][k], blocks};
}
```

