## Why This Is Asked
Tests a two-dimensional DP with an inner precomputation and path reconstruction, a common interview pattern for text/partition problems.

## Key Concepts
- Palindromic edit-cost precomputation (costPal).
- Partition DP with exactly k segments.
- Reconstruction of cut points and time/space trade-offs.

## Code Example
```javascript
function minPalPartitionCost(s, k) {
  const n = s.length;
  const costPal = Array.from({ length: n }, () => Array(n).fill(0));
  for (let i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    for (let j = i; j < n; j++) {
      if (i >= j) costPal[i][j] = 0;
      else costPal[i][j] = costPal[i + 1][j - 1] + (s[i] !== s[j] ? 1 : 0);
    }
  }
  const INF = 1e9;
  const dp = Array.from({ length: n + 1 }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(INF));
  const par = Array.from({ length: n + 1 }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-1));
  dp[0][0] = 0;
  for (let x = 1; x <= n; x++) {
    for (let t = 1; t <= k; t++) {
      for (let i = t - 1; i < x; i++) {
        const val = dp[i][t - 1] + costPal[i][x - 1];
        if (val < dp[x][t]) {
          dp[x][t] = val;
          par[x][t] = i;
        }
      }
    }
  }
  // reconstruction can follow from par
  return { cost: dp[n][k], cuts: par };
}
```

