## Why This Is Asked

Tests a fresh DP angle: combine subproblem best within intervals with partition into exactly k blocks, ensuring non-overlap and order.

## Key Concepts

- Precompute bestSubarray(l, r) for all intervals.
- Knapsack-style DP over blocks: dp[i][t] = max over l of dp[l-1][t-1] + bestSubarray(l, i).
- Reconstruction: store the chosen l for each dp[i][t].
- Complexity: O(n^2 k) time, O(n^2) for bestSubarray and O(nk) for DP.

## Code Example

```javascript
function solve(A, k) {
  const n = A.length;
  // 1) bestSubarray(l, r)
  const best = Array.from({ length: n }, () => Array(n).fill(-Infinity));
  for (let l = 0; l < n; l++) {
    let maxEnding = 0;
    let bestSoFar = -Infinity;
    for (let r = l; r < n; r++) {
      maxEnding = Math.max(A[r], maxEnding + A[r]);
      bestSoFar = Math.max(bestSoFar, maxEnding);
      best[l][r] = bestSoFar;
    }
  }
  // 2) DP over i, t
  const dp = Array.from({ length: n }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-Infinity));
  const par = Array.from({ length: n }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-1));
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) dp[i][1] = best[0][i], par[i][1] = -2;
  for (let t = 2; t <= k; t++) {
    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
      let bestVal = -Infinity, bestL = -1;
      for (let l = t - 1; l <= i; l++) {
        const cand = (l - 1 >= 0 ? dp[l - 1][t - 1] : 0) + best[l][i];
        if (cand > bestVal) { bestVal = cand; bestL = l; }
      }
      dp[i][t] = bestVal;
      par[i][t] = bestL;
    }
  }
  // reconstruction omitted for brevity
  return { bestValue: dp[n - 1][k], blocks: [] };
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you optimize memory to O(nk)?
- How would you adapt if blocks must be exactly length L or gaps have a minimum size?

## Why This Is Asked
