- How would you optimize memory to O(m*K) and still reconstruct the path?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests DP over partitioning with an order-dependent gain, plus reconstruction. Distinct from standard sum-of-maximums or cooldown problems.

## Key Concepts

- Order-dependent block weighting
- Prefix sums for O(1) subarray sums
- 2D DP with backtracking pointers
- Time/space trade-offs and reconstruction

## Code Example

```javascript
function maxValue(A, k) {
  const n = A.length;
  const pref = new Array(n+1).fill(0);
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) pref[i+1] = pref[i] + A[i];
  const dp = Array.from({ length: n+1 }, () => Array(k+1).fill(-Infinity));
  const par = Array.from({ length: n+1 }, () => Array(k+1).fill(-1));
  dp[0][0] = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    for (let t = 1; t <= k; t++) {
      // end a block at i
      for (let j = 0; j <= i; j++) {
        const val = dp[j][t-1] + (pref[i+1] - pref[j]) * t;
        if (val > dp[i+1][t]) {
          dp[i+1][t] = val;
          par[i+1][t] = j;
        }
      }
      // skip i is implicit via dp[i+1][t] initialization from dp[i][t]
      if (dp[i][t] > dp[i+1][t]) {
        dp[i+1][t] = dp[i][t];
        par[i+1][t] = -2; // indicate skip
      }
    }
  }
  // Reconstruction omitted for brevity
  return dp[n][k];
}
```

